# AgentForce Infotech Slack Communication Guidelines

## Channel Usage

### Company-Wide Channels
- #agentforce-general - Company-wide announcements (read-only for most)
- #agentforce-engineering - Technical discussions, architecture
- #agentforce-random - Non-work conversations, team bonding
- #agentforce-help - Ask questions, get help from anyone
- #agentforce-announcements - Important company updates (read-only)

### Team Channels
- #agentforce-backend - Backend developers (Python, Django, APIs)
- #agentforce-frontend - Frontend developers (React, TypeScript)
- #agentforce-devops - Infrastructure, deployment, CI/CD
- #agentforce-qa - Quality assurance and testing
- #agentforce-product - Product discussions and requirements

### Project-Specific Channels
- #agentforce-phoenix - Phoenix project discussions
- #agentforce-atlas - Atlas project discussions
- #agentforce-hercules - Hercules project discussions

### Support Channels
- #agentforce-dev-support - Development environment issues
- #agentforce-it-helpdesk - IT support requests
- #agentforce-deployments - Deployment notifications and discussions
- #agentforce-incidents - Production incidents and status updates

## Best Practices

1. Use threads for replies to keep channels organized (especially in busy channels)
2. Use @channel sparingly (only for urgent, company-wide matters)
3. Use @here for messages relevant to currently online team members
4. Don't DM for questions that could help others (use public channels for knowledge sharing)
5. Set your status when away, in meetings, or on vacation
6. Use status emoji: üçï (lunch), üè• (sick), üèñÔ∏è (vacation), üîï (focus time)

## Response Times (IST - Indian Standard Time)

- Urgent (@here/@channel): Within 1 hour during business hours (9 AM - 6 PM IST)
- Normal messages: Within 4 business hours
- Non-urgent: Within 24 hours
- Weekend/after hours: Next business day (unless marked urgent)

## Etiquette

- Be respectful, professional, and inclusive
- Use emojis appropriately (üëç for acknowledgment, ‚úÖ for done, ‚ùå for issues)
- Don't send messages outside business hours (9 AM - 6 PM IST) unless urgent
- Use code blocks (```) for code snippets
- Tag relevant people when asking questions (@username)
- Use "Do Not Disturb" mode during focus time or meetings

## Status Updates

Update your Slack status for:
- Out of office (OOO)
- In meetings (with meeting name if helpful)
- Focus time / Do Not Disturb
- On vacation (with dates)
- Working from home (WFH)

## Channel Naming Convention

All channels follow: `agentforce-{team/project/topic}` format
- Team channels: agentforce-{team-name}
- Project channels: agentforce-{project-name}
- Topic channels: agentforce-{topic}

## Important Contacts

- IT Helpdesk: helpdesk@agentforce.com or #agentforce-it-helpdesk
- For urgent matters outside Slack: Call manager or use phone
- Slack Admin: Contact IT helpdesk for channel creation or access issues

For Slack questions or issues, contact IT helpdesk or post in #agentforce-help.
